  "texts": [
    "For instance given B cocat, a company node with a high closeness score indicates the company is connected, and thus it is close, to many category nodes which in turn are connected to several other company nodes.",
    "Lastly, betweenness centrality [97,102] assesses the level of influence a node holds over information flow within a graph.",
    "In the context of bipartite graphs, it identifies nodes serving as critical mediators in enabling interactions between the two separate node partitions [14].",
    "ESG-related actions' variabilityWe leverage information theory to assess the entropy of ESG topics based on their associated predicates yielded from companies' sustainability reports.",
    "Specifically, we adopt Shannon's entropy (Equation ( 1), [103]) to measure the information, and thus the variability, present in a set of events X through their respective occurrence probabilities p(x):H(X):= - x∈X p(x) ln p(x)."
  ]
}